<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6448&amp;p=62274#p62274"><![CDATA[
We can explain how the MMC3 works, but if you are making games for the PlayPower project you might want to reconsider using this mapper.<br /><br />I'm not familiar with the actual process used by the chinese manufacturers to make cartridges, but I'd assume MMC3 games would be harder and more expensive to make than the ones using simple discrete logic mappers (CNROM, UNROM).<br /><br />Does anyone here know anything about the chinese manufacturers? I know I have a couple of chinese multicarts that include MMC3 games, but I don't know if they are just as easy to make as the other ones.<br /><br />Also, if this is for the Typing Warrior game, I think that the MMC3 is overkill. I think this game has a simple design that would benefit little from the MMC3 features. Maybe you mean you want to use the MMC3 for another game?<br /><br />EDIT: Thanks koitsu!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Jun 02, 2010 7:55 am</p><hr />
